The path data is as follows:
- M 83.17,32.03: Move to the starting point (83.17, 32.03).
- L 87.90,19.01: Draw a line to (87.90, 19.01).
- L 76.80,8.19: Draw a line to (76.80, 8.19).
- L 69.67,12.38: Draw a line to (69.67, 12.38).
- L 72.92,22.11: Draw a line to (72.92, 22.11).
- M 72.92,22.11: Move to (72.92, 22.11) (this is redundant as it is already at this point).
- L 83.17,32.03: Draw a line back to the starting point (83.17, 32.03).

The path forms a closed shape with five distinct points, which suggests it is a pentagon. Let's verify this by plotting the points and connecting them according to the path instructions.
